text: The food is not bad, Xiao Long Bao is above average in Singapore.

#1st review#
The stall prepares their dumplings and baos fresh every day. Today, I had the opportunity to try the following:
1. Xiao long bao - It was juicy and delicious. Definitely a dish I would order again.
2. Hot and sour soup - The spiciness was just right. Personally, I found it slightly sweet, but I believe locals would enjoy this flavor profile.
3. Sheng jian bao

#2nd review (two weeks later)#
Today I tried the spicy chili oil wanton and I really enjoyed it. The wanton skin was smooth, and the filling was delicious. Moreover, the sauce was flavorful and added an extra kick to the dish.

Sheng jian bao is not bad, not the overly oily type. Seasoning is quite balance. Ordered Seaweed and black fungus was given a big one instead of small one. Taste wise was not bad prefer the black fungus over the seaweed. Will come back and try the xlb.

Delicious crispy and juicy handmade pork bao and juicy handmade Xiao long bao.
Bao 4 pcs for $6.50 enough for 2
XLB $6.50 for 5

Downside - Semi industrial food court with annoying “bell” to alert you to orders ready. Busier means more annoying

First time bought Sheng Jian Bao from this stall was way back in Oct 2022…. They tasted really good & 4 pieces were really not enough!

4 months later, I went back to the same place but this time I was a bit disappointed…. The bao is not as crispy like before & there is also lesser “soup” inside the bao…

& the 口感also not as good as before :-(

The difference can be seen between the pictures…. 1st two were taken in Oct 2022 & 3rd one taken in Mar 2023…
